headline: 3 Reasons to Buy Realty Income Stock Like There's No Tomorrow
summary: Interest rates are a big deal for real estate investment trusts (REITs) because these property owners make extensive use of debt to fund deals.  The current volatile interest-rate environment has crushed the REIT sector, which is down around 10% over the past three months as the market's interest-rate expectations have notably shifted.  Realty Income (NYSE: O) is down even more, having lost about 15% of its value over the same span.
